# Development Environment
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
SESSION_SECRET=your-random-session-secret-min-32-chars

# ===== SUPABASE DATABASE (Required for Supabase Mode) =====
# Get these from: https://supabase.com
# 1. Create a Supabase account and project
# 2. Go to Project Settings → API
# 3. Copy the credentials below

SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ===== OPTIONAL: Gemini AI API =====
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key

# ===== NOTES =====
# - For SQLite (default): Comment out SUPABASE_* variables
# - For Supabase: Fill in SUPABASE_* variables and follow SUPABASE_SETUP.md
# - SESSION_SECRET: Generate a strong random string (min 32 characters)
#   Example: openssl rand -base64 32
